LEX Escrow


"Buyer" is	 a person

"Payee" is A person

"Arbiter" is  a person

"Fee" is	aN  amount


The Buyer pays an amount into escrow, appoints the Payee, appoints the Arbiter, and fixes the Fee


CLAUSE: Pay Out

The Arbiter may pay from escrow the Fee to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the Payee


CLAUSE: Pay Back

The Arbiter may pay from escrow the Fee to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the Buyer


